Although pitchers [[Randy Johnson]], [[Bill Risley]], and [[Bobby Ayala]] combined for an opening-day three-hit [[shutout]], the Mariners' {{By|1995}} season started off on a bad note overall, as Griffey sustained a major early-season injury. Despite this loss, the Mariners continued to play fairly well, guided by Piniella.
